Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Receipteze makes sending and managing receipts easy. Receipteze is an online service allowing the sending and receiving of receipts, and the management thereof. It allows introducing receipts into an account by way of having a person or business send a receipt, inputting them manually, forwarding receipt emails, or by allowing Receipteze to automatically pick receipts out from an email inbox. In the future lots of more features and functionality will be added making Receipteze more dynamic and more flexible, including a developer interface. Individuals can send a receipt to another individual for any transaction or payment received. They can also manage and keep track of online receipts, any receipts in an electronic format and brought into an account, and any physical receipts that are introduced. In addition purchases can easily be shared with others online. Basically, Receipteze allows anything one could possibly want to do with receipts. Businesses can send a receipt acknowledging a monetary transaction, or confirm something like the return of a borrowed item.  They can offer customers the electronic receipt option, manage and keep track of all the receipts they've distributed, handle item returns, cut back on using receipt paper, and cut back on receipt chemicals being exposed to their customers and employees.  Also they can help savvy customers not worry about losing receipts, unclutter customers' email inboxes and/or homes of receipts, and in the future, get a developer to easily automate it all in a short amount of time with Receipteze's interface.

Description: Smart Bible Search uses search engine technology to give you accurate results ordered by relevance.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Smart Bible Search uses the latest search engine technology to give you accurate results ordered by relevance. As you type, Bible passages are auto suggested to further help find passages. Smart Bible Search uses complex algorithms to return the passages you really wanted. Our algorithms fall into several categories to make this happen which are listed below with description and definitions of each. WORD FOR WORD (Literal) Results based on what you would see in the passage. How most Bible search sites return results   DYNAMIC EQUIVALENT (Thought for Thought) The search does not have to be perfect, or even contain the actual words you are typing. Search examples would be “Jesus is God”, “The Holy Spirit Convicts of Sin”, “lineage of Melchizedek”, “buried investment in the yard” and “Pregnancy of Mary”. AMBIGUOUS  A good example would be the phrase “I Am”. On any traditional search engine the search for “I Am” would return results that would be irrelevant, since it is not realizing the significance of the phrase. When a search for “I Am” is made on Smart Bible Search, it is understood that you are referring to a search for Jesus as the “I Am.” Another semi-ambiguous example would be the search for “Pauls Thorn”. CONCEPTUAL Returns results for Biblical concepts that are not specifically mentioned word for word in the bible, but are still inferred or are common terms and phrases used by Christians. Some examples would be “Trinity”, “Rapture”, “Christmas”, “Easter”, “Omnipresent”, “Omniscient” and “Omnipotent”. TOPICAL Returns relevant topical results based on single keywords, such as “Prayer”, “Salvation”, “Abortion” and “Sin”. These latest technologies results in the very accurate and relevant search results.

Description: Your starting point for online shopping.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: iBrow.se is your personalized starting point for online shopping. Today, people's online shopping preferences are scattered across silos (e.g. individual online stores) and general purpose tools (e.g. email, browser bookmarks, etc.).   Because of this, your shopping preferences get lost, like the link to that cool store you found that's now lost in the middle of unorganized browser bookmarks, or they clutter up more important things, like the dozen deal emails that come into your inbox every day from stores and obscure messages from friends and family. iBrow.se simplifies, centralizes, and personalizes your online shopping experience, by creating a personal starting point for online shopping that aggregates and organizes your shopping preferences (e.g. your favorite stores, deals, etc.), so that they're easily accessible when you want to go shopping. Lastly, in addition to aggregating your preferences and making the easily accessible, iBrow.se also helps you discover more stores and more deals that you might like, based on your preferences.  So, not only is it easier to shop at your favorite stores, but it's also easy to discover new favorite stores from the thousands of amazing online stores out there, where you can find great products for yourself or gifts for friends and family.
